    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-27T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-27T11:00:00-05:00" n="601"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 EW/8–2745: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crocker</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-27T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 27, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:49 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1812. Deptel 1366, August 18.<note n="33" xml:id="d601fn33">Not printed.</note>
                    British, French and American Missions Saturday<note n="34" xml:id="d601fn34"
                        >August 25.</note> presented identical notes to Foreign Office addressed to
                        Salazar<note n="34a" xml:id="d601fn34a">Antonio de Oliveira Salazar,
                        President of Portuguese Council of Ministers, and Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs.</note> requesting Portuguese Government’s assistance in <pb
                        facs="0816" n="806" xml:id="pg_806"/> effecting repatriation of German
                    officials and agents. Director of Political Affairs to whom notes were handed
                    reacted along general lines of Embtel 1577, July 23 but ultimate decision
                    depends on Dr. Salazar and we will press for formal reply. Despatch
                        follows.<note n="35" xml:id="d601fn35">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Dept, repeated to Madrid as 193, London as 422, Paris as 288.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crocker</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
